  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add your <strong>basmati rice</strong>, a pinch of<strong> salt </strong>and 300ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[390ml]</span><span class=\"text-danger\"> [600ml]</span> <strong>cold water</strong> to a pot with a lid and bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Once boiling, add your <strong>cardamom pods</strong> and reduce the heat to very low and cook, covered, for 10-12 min or until all the water has absorbed and the rice is cooked – this is your <strong>fragrant</strong> <strong>rice</strong></p><p>Once cooked, remove from the heat and keep covered until serving</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1608563007543-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1608563007543-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1608563007543-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1608563007543-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1608563007543-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Boil half a kettle</p><p>Whilst the rice is cooking, peel and finely chop your <strong>brown onion[s]</strong></p><p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a generous drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong> over a medium heat</p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>chopped onion</strong> with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and cook for 5-6 min or until starting to soften</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1608563012522-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1608563012522-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1608563012522-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1608563012522-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1608563012522-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, peel and finely chop (or grate) your <strong>garlic</strong></p><p>Dice your <strong>tomato[es]</strong> finely</p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1608562973681-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1608562973681-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1608562973681-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1608562973681-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1608562973681-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once the onion has started to soften, add the <strong>chopped garlic</strong>,<strong> ginger paste</strong>, <strong>curry powder </strong>and <strong>ground paprika</strong> to the pan, then cook for 1-2 min or until fragrant</p><p>Once fragrant, add the <strong>diced tomato</strong> and cook for 3-4 min or until the veg has broken down to make a thick sauce</p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1608562968120-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1608562968120-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1608562968120-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1608562968120-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1608562968120-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, chop your <strong>creamed coconut </strong>roughly (if required!)</p><p>Dissolve the <strong>chopped</strong> <strong>creamed coconut</strong>, <strong>tomato paste </strong>and <strong>vegetable stock mix</strong> in 150ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[195ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[200ml]</span><strong> boiled water</strong> – this is your<strong> creamy tomato stock</strong></p><p>Once the veg has broken down, add the<strong> creamy tomato stock</strong> and<strong> </strong>most of your <strong>creamy single soy </strong>(save a small splash for serving!)<strong> </strong>and cook for 4-5 min or until the sauce is starting to thicken</p>",
      "order": 5,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-1608562956828-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-1608562956828-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-1608562956828-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-1608562956828-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-1608562956828-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Whilst the sauce is thickening, chop your <strong>meat-free chick'n </strong>into small bite-sized pieces</p><p>Chop your <strong>coriander</strong> finely, including the stalks</p>",
      "order": 6,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-6-1608562951510-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-6-1608562951510-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-6-1608562951510-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-6-1608562951510-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-6-1608562951510-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once the sauce has started to thicken, stir through the <strong>chopped</strong> <strong>meat-free chick'n </strong>and cook for 2-3 min further or until warmed through –this is your <strong>plant-based</strong> <strong>no butter chick'n</strong></p><p>Discard the <strong>cardamom pods</strong> from the fragrant rice</p>",
      "order": 7,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-7-1608562945502-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-7-1608562945502-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-7-1608562945502-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-7-1608562945502-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-7-1608562945502-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Serve the <strong>plant-based no butter chick'n</strong> over the <strong>fragrant rice</strong></p><p>Drizzle over the <strong>remaining creamy single soy</strong> and garnish with the <strong>chopped coriander</strong></p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
      "order": 8,
